&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Physiotherapy Assistant to join our Physiotherapy Team at Bexhill Irvine Unit&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be required to assist our Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists, with physical rehabilitation and general care of the patient which on occasions may be unsupervised. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will also be responsible for ensuring administrative requirements are completed on a daily basis, and manage the distribution of mobility equipment as required. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have excellent interpersonal skills, a caring approach and be willing to undertake training as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous physiotherapy experience within a relevant health or social care setting and a NVQ would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJulie-Anne NeussJob titleTeam Lead Physiotherapist - Bexhill Irvine UnitEmail addressjulie-anne.neuss@nhs.netTelephone number03001314430&lt;/p&gt;
